<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM1.5.8">
<l>uṉṉaiyu mokkalaiyiṟ koṇṭuta milmaruvi</l>
<l rend="indent">yuṉṉoṭu taṅkaḷkarut tāyiṉa ceytuvarum</l>
<l>kaṉṉiya rummakiḻak kaṇṭavar kaṇkuḷirak</l>
<l rend="indent">kaṟṟavar teṟṟivarap peṟṟave ṉakkaruḷi</l>
<l>maṉṉuku ṟuṅkuṭiyāy veḷḷaṟai yāymatilcūḻ</l>
<l rend="indent">cōlaima laikkaracē kaṇṇapu rattamutē</l>
<l>yeṉṉava lamkaḷaivā yāṭuka ceṅkīrai</l>
<l rend="indent">yēḻula kummuṭaiyā yāṭuka vāṭukavē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>So that the maidens who come, having grasped you to [their] hips</l>
<l rend="indent">join together with you in their houses [and] their desires accomplished, rejoice,</l>
<l>so that the eyes of those who see are refreshed,</l>
<l rend="indent">so that scholars come stumbling,</l>
<l>having graced me who begot [you], You of eternal Kuṟuṅkuṭi,</l>
<l rend="indent">You of Veḷḷaṟai, O King of Cōlaimalai, surrounded by walls,</l>
<l>O Nectar of Kaṇṇapuram, You who removes my suffering, please dance!</l>
<l rend="indent">You who possesses the seven worlds, dance the Ceṅkīrai, please dance!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
